DESCRIPTION
Job summary
Are you excited by the disruptive potential of quantum technology? Do you want to help businesses understand the challenges and opportunities of quantum computing (QC) and develop new practical use cases?

The quantum computing specialist team based in Tokyo, Japan is looking to hire a Quantum Solutions Specialist with knowledge of quantum computing and cloud computing fundamentals. Quantum Computing is a technology that holds promise to be transformational in many industries. To help our customers on this journey we are looking for a candidate who will work with academic, enterprise and startup customers to architect advanced solutions leveraging AWS Quantum Computing services, collaborate with service and business stakeholders, and grow the AWS quantum computing ecosystem.

The ideal candidate will possess a deeply technical background and a strong drive to solve practical problems using quantum computers in the cloud. The candidate will have the technical depth and business experience to easily communicate the potential and challenges of Quantum Computing, multiple hardware platforms and frameworks in the AWS cloud to scientists, managers, and engineering teams. The candidate will also collaborate with customers and internal research teams to deliver innovative solutions. This requires familiarity with state-of-the-art approaches to quantum computing, its target use cases, and knowledge of high-performance computing, parallel computing and cloud computing fundamentals.

This is an opportunity to be at the forefront of science and technological transformations.


Key job responsibilities
Architect advanced solutions leveraging AWS Quantum Computing services, working closely with our customers to deeply understand their business needs and to design technical solutions that take advantage of the AWS Cloud platform and Quantum Computing services;
Demonstrate the viability of each solution through mechanisms like proof-of-concepts or prototypes;
Develop compelling audience-specific messages and tools (presentations, product videos, customer success stories, advanced demos, white papers, how to guides, etc.)
Evangelize AWS Quantum Computing services and technologies through forums such as AWS Blogs, magazine articles, and public-speaking events at workshops and conferences;
Collaborate with AWS field sales, professional services, training and support teams to help partners and customers learn and effectively use AWS Quantum Computing services;
Collaborate with internal teams to define the product road map, market positioning and developer program initiatives.


About the team
You will be joining the quantum computing specialist team. We are the in-house experts in quantum computing who work with customers to find new use cases of quantum technologies, promote the use of the Amazon Braket service, and push the boundary of knowledge by developing new large-scale scientific applications that have broader commercial use. Our team members deliver for customers by publishing blog posts, research papers, and giving high-visibility talks at premier workshops and conferences.

Our team is dedicated to supporting new members. We have a broad mix of experience levels and tenures, and we provide an environment that celebrates knowledge sharing and mentorship. We care about employee career growth and strive to assign projects based on what will help each team member develop into a better-rounded individual and enable them to take on more complex tasks in the future.
BASIC QUALIFICATIONS
3+ years of design, implementation, or consulting experience in applications or infrastructures
8+ years within specific technology domain areas (e.g. software development, cloud computing, systems engineering, infrastructure, security, networking, data & analytics)

MS in a quantum computation related field (Quantum Physics, Quantum Chemistry, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics);
3+ years of experience with Quantum Computing and familiarity with basic use cases in chemistry, optimization, and machine learning;
Knowledge of cloud computing fundamentals and understanding of how businesses use the cloud;
Hands-on experience in a high-level programming language (Python, Java, C/C++...);
Demonstrated ability to collaborate effectively with multiple teams and thrive in a fast-paced environment;
Strong verbal and written communications skills.
PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS
Ph.D. in a quantum computation related field (Quantum Physics, Quantum Chemistry, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics);
5+ years of experience using quantum simulators or quantum computers;
3+ years of experience with high-performance computing (HPC), parallel computing and distributed systems;
Relevant industry experience or experience with sales engineering to Fortune 1000 and/or Global 2000 organizations.



