DESCRIPTION
Job summary
Are you excited by the disruptive potential of quantum technology? Do you want to help the Intelligence Community understand the challenges and opportunities of quantum computing (QC) and develop new practical use cases?

The Emerging Technology team based near Washington, D.C. is looking to hire a Principal Quantum Technologist with significant experience with quantum computing hardware and/or algorithms. Quantum Computing is a technology that holds promise to be transformational for National Security. To help our customers on this journey we are looking for a candidate who will work with government agencies, academic and technology partners to architect advanced solutions leveraging AWS Quantum Computing services as well as be a trusted advisor and thought leader to help grow the quantum computing ecosystem at a national level.

The ideal candidate will possess a combination of scientific background, technology leadership, and a strong drive to solve practical problems using quantum computers in the cloud. The candidate will have the technical depth and business experience to easily communicate the potential and challenges of Quantum Computing, multiple hardware platforms and frameworks to executives, scientists, and engineering teams. The candidate will also collaborate with customers and internal research teams to solve complex problems and publish results. This requires deep familiarity with state-of-the-art approaches to quantum computing, as well as target use cases using HPC and ML in the cloud.

This is an opportunity to be at the forefront of science and technological transformations at global level.

Key job responsibilities
Advise and support agency leaders to better understand how Quantum capabilities will impact and further the national security mission.
Architect advanced solutions leveraging AWS Quantum Computing services, working closely with our customers to deeply understand their business needs and to design technical solutions that take advantage of the AWS Cloud platform and Quantum Computing services;
Demonstrate the viability of each solution through mechanisms like proof-of-concepts or prototypes, research projects, and white papers.
Participate and collaborate as a trusted adviser and thought leader in industry associations and Quantum related advisory committees.
Publish research results obtained in collaboration with internal research teams or customers in journals and conferences and AWS blogs to promote AWS Quantum Computing services;
Evangelize AWS Quantum Computing services and technologies by developing compelling audience-specific messages and tools (product videos, customer success stories, advanced demos, how to guides, etc.);
Gain recognition and credibility as a presenter, panelist and keynote speaker for multiple internal and external workshops and conferences;
Collaborate with AWS field sales, professional services, training and support teams to help partners and customers learn and effectively use AWS Quantum Computing services;
Collaborate with internal teams to define the product road map, market positioning and developer program initiatives.


A day in the life
The right candidate will be a guiding voice in the Quantum community. Their typical day will include leading development of advanced Quantum applications and solutions for National Security. You will also lead executive engagements with government customers and policymakers, support strategy reviews with AWS stakeholders, and create public and customer facing content to help the community understand and adopt Quantum technologies. As such, customer engagement, training, and enablement are critical daily tasks.

About the team
Our team specializes in Emerging Technologies, and we pride ourselves on our deep technical and mission knowledge. AWS customers turn to us as experts and Trusted Advisors to help them adopt AI/ML, Quantum, and other technologies.

Internally, our team is hyper-collaborative, we think long term, and we put a high value on work-life balance. It isn’t about how many hours you spend at home or at work; it’s about the flow you establish that brings energy to both parts of your life. We believe striking the right balance between your personal and professional life is critical to life-long happiness and fulfillment. We offer flexibility in working hours and encourage you to find your own balance between your work and personal lives.

Our team is dedicated to supporting new associates. We have a broad mix of experience levels and tenures, and we’re building an environment that celebrates knowledge sharing and mentorship. We care about your career growth and strive to assign projects based on what will help each team member develop into a better-rounded professional and enable them to take on more complex tasks in the future.
BASIC QUALIFICATIONS
PhD in a quantum computation related field (Quantum Physics, Quantum Chemistry, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics)
5+ years of experience with Quantum Computing including strong quantum hardware or algorithm domain knowledge;
Demonstrated ability to gain insights that drive new technology use cases in quantum computing and suggest service improvements that can be adopted by the business;
Demonstrated ability to collaborate effectively with multiple teams and thrive in a fast-paced environment;
Strong verbal and written communications skills.
PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS
3+ years of experience developing and maturing Quantum or related emerging technology companies, business units, or government programs.
3+ years of experience using gate-based quantum computers (superconducting, ion trap, neutral atom, photonic qubits, etc.), analog quantum simulators, or annealers;
2+ years of research experience with quantum algorithms that have practical applications in chemistry, optimization, or machine learning;
Strong knowledge and industry experience with distributed systems, and service-oriented architecture;
Experience with cloud computing and or related fields (IT, software, etc.);
Experience with sales engineering to Fortune 1000 and/or Global 2000 organizations.
Demonstrable knowledge of intelligence community procurement, contracting processes, RDT&E, and the National Quantum Initiative.


